edu.udel.cis.taschd.skill

Class SkillSet

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.udel.cis.taschd.skill.SkillSet

  • public class SkillSet
extends java.lang.Object

    The SkillSet is a unordered set of Skills representing a collection of abilities. Examples include the skill set of a CourseAssistant, which corresponds to the classes which a CourseAssistant can be assigned, or the skill set of a CourseInstance, which corresponds to the mandatory set of skills required for a Course.

    SkillSet is a Set of Skills.

      • SkillSet

        public SkillSet(java.util.Collection<Skill> skillSet)
        Constructs a new SkillSet from the given collection of strings. The new SkillSet will not keep any reference to the given Skill (String), hence subsequent modifications to the collection will not affect the new SkillSet. The new SkillSet may keep references to the member skills of the collection, but since Skills (Strings) are immutable, this fact should be invisible to the client. The internal representation may differ from the organization of the collection, in that Skills will be unordered and duplicates removed. The given Collection will not be modified.
        Parameters:
        skillSet - a collection of non-null Skills that will be used to build the new SkillSet.
